contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:55.440 --> 01:57.602
Landscape is destiny.

02:00.360 --> 02:03.842
I've carried that phrase
in my head for years now.

02:05.560 --> 02:09.086
I can't remember where it comes from,
but I know what it means here.

02:10.160 --> 02:13.289
It's a sense of being closed in.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.401
Human limitation.

02:20.040 --> 02:21.660
It's different from the Midwest,

02:21.760 --> 02:26.163
where possibility sprawls bright
and endless in every direction.

02:27.280 --> 02:31.080
People in the Himalayas, the Andes,

02:32.920 --> 02:36.242
do they live in the passive voice, too?

02:38.880 --> 02:41.326
Like their lives aren't real?

02:42.080 --> 02:46.927
Their memories, fixed,

02:48.440 --> 02:50.204
immutable.

03:54.557 --> 03:56.641
That'll be $1.57.

03:57.520 --> 04:00.000
I can take one of 'em off, if you want?

04:05.160 --> 04:06.491
All right, don't worry about it.

04:06.960 --> 04:08.803
- Hey.
- Shut up.

04:09.120 --> 04:10.770
All right. You have a good day now.

04:11.160 --> 04:12.321
Travis?

04:13.000 --> 04:14.331
What just happened here?

04:15.080 --> 04:17.082
Did you let somebody
walk out of here without paying?

04:17.360 --> 04:19.420
You can't quit! You're fired!

04:19.519 --> 04:22.251
If you come back,
I'll have you turned in.

06:50.760 --> 06:52.000
Leave it.

07:19.440 --> 07:20.726
Where have you been?

07:20.840 --> 07:22.220
I called your place.

07:22.320 --> 07:24.971
You know my dad. It don't matter.

07:26.680 --> 07:27.681
Hey.

07:27.880 --> 07:30.500
You ain't gonna believe what I got
in the back of this here truck.

07:30.600 --> 07:31.601
What?

07:35.440 --> 07:37.204
Holy shit!

07:38.480 --> 07:41.260
Just fuckin' found 'em
while I was fishing at the river.

07:41.360 --> 07:42.885
Well, what are you gonna do with it?

07:43.040 --> 07:46.044
Sell 'em, I guess,
if I can figure out who to.

07:49.640 --> 07:51.244
Leonard Shuler will take 'em.

07:51.960 --> 07:54.042
- You reckon?
- Oh, yeah.

07:55.000 --> 07:56.700
Yeah, he'll give you
good money for these.

07:56.800 --> 07:59.963
- Why? He don't know me.
- Well, he knows me.

08:07.220 --> 08:08.167
Shit!

08:08.960 --> 08:11.804
Aw, don't mind them. They're all noise.

08:18.600 --> 08:20.090
He always carry that?

08:20.240 --> 08:21.700
Hell, yeah.

08:21.800 --> 08:26.089
You know, he used to be a teacher
up north, but they kicked his ass out.

08:26.200 --> 08:29.170
The way I heard it
is that he shot some fellow.

08:30.920 --> 08:32.251
Hey, Leonard.

08:32.880 --> 08:34.847
Shank. Who's this?

08:35.600 --> 08:38.284
This here is Travis Shelton.
He's a buddy of mine.

08:40.480 --> 08:43.051
Shelton? You from the Laurel?

08:43.200 --> 08:44.380
No.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.323
My daddy grew up there.

08:48.600 --> 08:52.180
Well, if it's weed you're after,
you're out of luck.

08:52.280 --> 08:56.171
I only got three dime bags at present
and I won't have more till Monday.

08:56.760 --> 09:00.446
Well, looks like we've
come at the right time.

09:00.640 --> 09:02.369
Let's show him.

09:14.320 --> 09:16.482
- Where'd you get these?
- Found them.

09:18.000 --> 09:20.128
Figure finders keepers?

09:26.840 --> 09:28.569
Looks like you dragged them
through a Haybine.

09:28.920 --> 09:30.340
Aw, there's plenty of buzz left.

09:30.440 --> 09:32.886
Really, come on.
How much will you give me for 'em?

09:35.560 --> 09:36.971
Forty bucks.

09:38.120 --> 09:39.645
Nah. Give me $50.

09:42.960 --> 09:44.405
All right.

09:56.320 --> 09:57.890
Put 'em over there in the weeds.

09:58.880 --> 10:00.006
On my tomatoes.

10:03.760 --> 10:07.810
I was thinking that maybe you might
sweeten the deal. How 'bout a beer?

10:10.040 --> 10:12.281
Beer is in the icebox. Help yourself.

10:26.160 --> 10:27.286
Hey.

10:30.720 --> 10:32.404
Hey, show him the pistol.

10:34.160 --> 10:37.403
So that is some
real Dirty Harry shit right there.

10:38.400 --> 10:40.260
Leonard here is a hell of a shot.

10:40.360 --> 10:42.408
He can hit a chigger's ass at 200 feet.

10:43.880 --> 10:46.724
Why don't you let Travis
hold that sweetheart for a second?

10:47.080 --> 10:48.241
I don't think so.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.460
What's that?

10:57.560 --> 10:59.483
That's a metal detector.

10:59.760 --> 11:03.162
A guy wanted some dope, came up short
and used it as collateral.

11:04.400 --> 11:06.482
I use it to find Civil War relics.

11:07.800 --> 11:09.404
What are we listenin' to?

11:10.600 --> 11:12.682
Appalachian Spring by Copland.

11:13.240 --> 11:14.460
I've never heard of him.

11:14.560 --> 11:16.085
He used to open for Skynyrd.

11:20.440 --> 11:22.442
Well, they sound like shit.

11:23.280 --> 11:25.660
- No, it doesn't.
- It does to me.

11:25.760 --> 11:30.322
Well, that's probably because you fail
to empathize with his view of the region.

11:31.280 --> 11:32.281
What?

11:33.800 --> 11:36.246
Oh, y'all got a bathroom in this palace?

11:47.320 --> 11:49.209
I'm just fucking with you, Shank.

11:49.800 --> 11:50.961
I know.

11:54.000 --> 11:56.446
Take your foot off my coffee table.

12:28.400 --> 12:31.722
"December 21st, 1859.

12:33.280 --> 12:37.001
"Naomi Luis, age 22.

12:38.520 --> 12:41.444
"Complaint, sore eyes.

12:43.120 --> 12:47.808
"Diagnosis, optical inflammation
due to handling mistletoe.

12:49.040 --> 12:54.683
"Treatment, wash made of infusion
of goldenseal root in cold water.

12:55.960 --> 12:57.928
"Use twice daily.

13:00.840 --> 13:02.444
"Fee,

13:03.360 --> 13:07.285
"$1 and a quarter. Paid cash."

13:36.560 --> 13:37.925
What do you want?

13:40.680 --> 13:42.728
Come here for a show, is that it?

13:44.040 --> 13:45.201
No.

13:45.600 --> 13:46.931
No?

13:50.840 --> 13:52.808
What's the matter?
You don't like what you see?

13:54.960 --> 13:56.610
Leonard?

13:57.800 --> 13:59.211
All right, boys.

14:00.040 --> 14:01.929
How 'bout one more for the road?

14:02.040 --> 14:03.041
No.

14:05.920 --> 14:08.366
So I take it
you've never been up to Shelton Laurel.

14:10.440 --> 14:12.920
Just family reunions when I was a kid.

14:13.560 --> 14:16.609
Did your daddy ever mention anything
about Bloody Madison to you?

14:17.040 --> 14:18.326
No. What's that?

14:18.600 --> 14:21.285
It's the name this county
went by during the war.

14:23.720 --> 14:26.530
Yeah, you know, I think
my uncle said something once.

14:26.680 --> 14:28.740
That some little kid got killed there

14:28.840 --> 14:30.171
- during the war.
- Killed by who?

14:30.520 --> 14:32.340
Shit, I don't know. Yankees, I guess.

14:32.440 --> 14:33.646
You never asked.

14:35.680 --> 14:37.444
You make it sound like I'm ignorant.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.240
Maybe a little.

14:41.160 --> 14:42.810
Take that shirt you're wearing.

14:42.960 --> 14:46.851
You know if you'd worn that around here in
the 1860s, it would have gotten you killed,

14:46.960 --> 14:48.660
most likely by your own kin.

14:48.760 --> 14:50.603
My people weren't Yankees.

14:50.960 --> 14:53.327
They didn't see any reason
to side with the slave owners.

14:54.320 --> 14:56.243
So, what are you saying?
They were on neither side.

14:56.360 --> 14:57.600
Oh, they had a side.

14:58.640 --> 15:01.769
Couldn't just sit it out, not up here.
Nobody could just sit it out.

15:02.640 --> 15:07.123
In most places,
battle would come, move on.

15:07.760 --> 15:10.001
War came to Madison and stayed.

15:12.520 --> 15:14.602
Hey, we goin' or what?

15:20.680 --> 15:24.366
Hey. We'll fucking get you
some more plants.

15:24.640 --> 15:26.210
I wouldn't advise that.

15:26.760 --> 15:28.620
A smart man would quit
when he was ahead.

15:28.720 --> 15:30.643
Well, didn't you just
tell me I was ignorant.

15:49.680 --> 15:52.524
Travis! You little shit.

15:53.240 --> 15:55.527
Get your ass out of bed.

15:55.720 --> 15:56.721
Now!

16:04.600 --> 16:05.601
Shit.

16:08.240 --> 16:09.844
- Come on.
- All right. Now try it.

16:15.540 --> 16:16.690
I got nothing.

16:17.200 --> 16:18.201
All right.

16:20.200 --> 16:22.806
Hey, we still got kin in Shelton Laurel?

16:24.200 --> 16:26.300
Yeah. Yeah. Why?

16:26.400 --> 16:27.731
I'm just wondering.

16:27.840 --> 16:30.286
Yeah. A few. I ain't seen 'em in years.
Come on.

16:30.400 --> 16:32.209
Well, how come we never go visit?

16:32.560 --> 16:33.561
And say what?

16:38.920 --> 16:40.604
All right. Turn it over.

16:58.760 --> 16:59.761
Well?

17:01.520 --> 17:02.601
Well, what?

17:06.640 --> 17:08.210
Now what do you want me to do?

17:08.440 --> 17:11.046
How about you start by telling me
what went down in that job of yours?

17:12.440 --> 17:14.807
What? You think I didn't
know about that?

17:15.200 --> 17:18.010
Look, Travis, I don't care much
about what you do or where you go,

17:18.119 --> 17:21.380
but I sure in hell mind when you make me
look like trash in front of this community.

17:21.480 --> 17:23.289
Don't you walk away from me.

17:24.640 --> 17:26.210
I can't figure you out.

17:26.480 --> 17:28.801
It's like you got too much damn pride
to work a day,

17:28.960 --> 17:30.700
a day, like regular folks.

17:30.800 --> 17:35.010
Stocking shelves, stocking shelves,
that's way, way beneath you, isn't it?

17:36.480 --> 17:38.209
When was the last time
you had a damn job?

17:41.560 --> 17:43.483
Harvey, stop!

17:51.200 --> 17:53.601
That's enough. That's enough.

18:01.640 --> 18:03.005
Travis.

18:48.880 --> 18:51.380
Pick that shit up, will you?

18:51.480 --> 18:53.403
What the hell does it
look like I'm doin'?

18:53.560 --> 18:55.210
Call Dooley.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.162
Tell him we're gonna be
delivering Saturday.

19:31.240 --> 19:34.210
Well, well, look at this.

19:34.320 --> 19:35.940
I'll be damned.

19:36.040 --> 19:37.769
Near about cut off, looks like.

19:39.320 --> 19:41.620
We can take him down there
and stick him in the river,

19:41.720 --> 19:44.166
maybe he's fallen, drowned himself.

19:44.280 --> 19:48.205
Another one. Even Sheriff Spence...

19:48.560 --> 19:49.925
All right.

19:55.880 --> 19:58.087
This ain't gonna hurt much.

20:24.120 --> 20:25.406
Give him some water.

20:33.960 --> 20:35.200
Oh, God.

20:37.040 --> 20:38.405
You is lucky.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.889
Didn't tear any ligaments up.

20:41.880 --> 20:43.882
Barely grazed the bone.

20:44.360 --> 20:46.567
Don't get infected, you'll be fine.

20:51.000 --> 20:52.460
What did you do?

20:52.560 --> 20:54.688
Just shaved a little skin
off of your leg.

20:54.920 --> 20:57.127
Can't even tell it's a trap now.

20:58.440 --> 21:01.842
Looks like you just slipped
and skinned it up.

21:05.600 --> 21:07.364
Who's your people?

21:08.800 --> 21:10.689
My daddy's Harvey Shelton.

21:10.840 --> 21:12.330
Is that right?

21:12.600 --> 21:14.660
I would've figured you to be stouter.

21:14.760 --> 21:16.683
You must favor your ma.

21:16.960 --> 21:18.500
I'll need to get to a doctor.

21:18.600 --> 21:20.045
In time.

21:20.400 --> 21:22.687
Stick him down there in the river
before it's too late.

21:23.000 --> 21:26.527
- We ain't doin' that, so shut up about it.
- Shit.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.540
Now, the sooner me and you
get a few things clear,

21:31.640 --> 21:34.060
the quicker you get to a doctor,
you understand?

21:34.160 --> 21:35.207
Yes, sir.

21:35.360 --> 21:36.361
All right.

21:36.560 --> 21:38.164
Anybody asks,

21:38.880 --> 21:40.882
you slipped climbing up the gorge.

21:41.040 --> 21:42.540
Slipped...

21:42.640 --> 21:46.645
You never saw no crop,
you was never on my land,

21:47.080 --> 21:48.923
damn sure never saw me.

21:50.720 --> 21:52.529
- Got it?
- Yes, sir.

21:52.720 --> 21:54.131
He ain't gonna do it.

21:54.440 --> 21:56.460
Soon as he gets to that hospital,
he'll be testifying...

21:56.560 --> 21:59.300
No, I won't. I won't, I won't.
I swear to you, Mr. Toomey.

21:59.400 --> 22:00.561
Mr. Toomey, please, I swear to you.

22:00.680 --> 22:03.081
I swear to you,
I won't say nothing, I swear.

22:05.080 --> 22:06.445
Pick him up.

22:15.040 --> 22:16.249
Come on.

22:20.880 --> 22:22.500
Oh, shit!

22:22.600 --> 22:23.931
- God!
- Get up.

22:32.960 --> 22:34.450
One more thing.

22:35.040 --> 22:36.769
Who did you sell those plants to?

22:37.120 --> 22:38.740
Leonard Shuler.

22:38.840 --> 22:41.207
- Does he know where you got 'em?
- No, sir.

22:43.560 --> 22:44.561
All right.

23:01.920 --> 23:04.241
Now, I told you I'd get you here.

23:05.360 --> 23:09.046
I kept my word,
you see that you keep yours.

23:41.160 --> 23:43.380
- Carlton?
- Professor.

23:43.480 --> 23:45.369
What brings you around? Come on in.

23:48.680 --> 23:49.727
Hubert.

23:50.720 --> 23:52.340
I thought you got called up.

23:52.440 --> 23:55.140
My number one son here is 4-F.

23:55.240 --> 23:57.527
Draft board didn't say why.

23:57.680 --> 24:00.684
I got my own suspicions about that.

24:02.200 --> 24:05.170
Well, you're better off here, anyway.

24:05.960 --> 24:07.371
What can I do for you?

24:08.560 --> 24:11.340
I got some business to discuss with you.

24:11.440 --> 24:12.460
Okay.

24:12.560 --> 24:15.006
Especially seeing
how you got a new supplier and all.

24:19.720 --> 24:21.210
That boy.

24:25.720 --> 24:26.940
I didn't know you was growing.

24:27.040 --> 24:31.762
To be fair, our crops are new things.
His idea.

24:32.960 --> 24:34.450
Times are changin'.

24:34.680 --> 24:36.820
We gotta give the people what they want.

24:36.920 --> 24:38.604
Speaking of which,

24:39.480 --> 24:42.848
seven fourteens of
black beauties, even split.

24:43.200 --> 24:45.009
$100 will cover it.

24:56.400 --> 24:57.561
There you go.

24:58.600 --> 25:00.180
Much obliged, sir.

25:00.280 --> 25:01.281
Hey, babe.

25:04.080 --> 25:05.969
Still with you, I see.

25:06.960 --> 25:09.281
Must cut into your profits, though.

25:11.200 --> 25:14.647
She been rode hard,
but she's still pretty.

25:17.080 --> 25:21.210
We'll be happy to take her off your
hands if you're ever so inclined.

25:21.600 --> 25:24.285
But listen to me pontificating.

25:25.440 --> 25:27.602
Time I was on my way.

25:31.520 --> 25:33.124
Carlton, that boy,

25:34.520 --> 25:36.124
what'd you do to him?

25:38.280 --> 25:43.810
Let's just say
he's retired from the drug trade.

25:45.080 --> 25:46.969
I'll see you around, Professor.

26:03.720 --> 26:06.803
How you doin'? Not too much pain?

26:07.800 --> 26:09.325
I know you.

26:09.760 --> 26:12.730
Wasn't... We was in homeroom together.

26:13.480 --> 26:15.540
Right. Travis. Travis Shelton.

26:15.640 --> 26:17.847
Yeah. Lori.

26:18.000 --> 26:19.900
Right. Miss Heywood's class.

26:20.000 --> 26:21.684
- Right.
- Yeah.

26:22.320 --> 26:26.542
Well, you got your leg cut up
pretty good there, Travis Shelton.

26:27.120 --> 26:28.531
How does it feel?

26:28.640 --> 26:29.641
Oh, it's okay.

26:30.600 --> 26:32.409
So it hurts like hell, right?

26:32.800 --> 26:33.801
Yeah.

26:34.680 --> 26:37.160
Here. Let me help you with that.

26:42.200 --> 26:43.420
What you readin'?

26:43.520 --> 26:45.124
Oh, nothing. Just boring old stuff.

26:45.920 --> 26:47.365
Can I have a look?

26:47.840 --> 26:49.365
Yeah, sure, if you want.

26:52.360 --> 26:56.251
"Both the Union and the Confederate
planned their attack strategically. They..."

26:57.360 --> 27:00.125
Oh, we were learnin'
about this in history, right?

27:00.560 --> 27:02.244
Oh. Yeah, right.

27:03.040 --> 27:04.201
I was just...

27:05.160 --> 27:09.768
You know about all the stories Sherman...
This whole scorched earth thing he did.

27:14.200 --> 27:15.690
Can I get you anything?

27:18.040 --> 27:19.724
Cigarette would be nice.

27:20.200 --> 27:22.202
Oh, I don't smoke.

27:24.880 --> 27:26.405
And neither should you.

27:55.800 --> 27:58.007
- Rubber bands.
- Rubber bands.

28:06.280 --> 28:07.930
I brought you some books.

28:09.480 --> 28:10.481
Here you go.

28:11.760 --> 28:13.364
To keep you company.

28:13.960 --> 28:16.884
Well, you know, I'm getting out real soon,
how am I gonna get 'em back to you?

28:17.000 --> 28:18.331
Can I call you here?

28:19.160 --> 28:20.161
Sure.

28:21.120 --> 28:22.724
Got a number or...

28:23.680 --> 28:24.806
Yeah.

28:27.360 --> 28:29.966
- You got a...
- You want to write on my hand.

28:30.400 --> 28:31.401
Sure.

28:40.640 --> 28:41.880
Here you go.

28:44.240 --> 28:47.449
- Don't forget and wash it off.
- I'll not do that.

28:50.960 --> 28:52.291
Bye.

28:59.320 --> 29:01.004
Does it still hurt?

29:01.400 --> 29:03.846
Doctor says I can be out
day after tomorrow.

29:06.400 --> 29:08.164
Then what are you gonna do?

29:10.080 --> 29:11.081
I don't know.

29:11.840 --> 29:14.020
Shank's got some friends
who own an auto shop.

29:14.120 --> 29:15.690
They said they were
gonna give me some hours.

29:17.400 --> 29:20.688
But what about a place to live?

29:24.640 --> 29:28.440
I just think that
you shouldn't come home right now.

29:29.240 --> 29:32.050
- Just for a while.
- Is that what he told you to say?

29:33.280 --> 29:35.123
He's angry, Travis.

29:35.680 --> 29:39.401
You dented his pride
saying those things you did.

29:39.760 --> 29:42.140
- You know how he is.
- Yeah. He's an asshole.

29:42.240 --> 29:45.722
The two of you goin' at it all the time.

29:46.440 --> 29:50.206
I just want some peace
in my house for once.

30:32.040 --> 30:33.610
What the hell are you doin' here?

30:36.640 --> 30:38.404
I got no place else to go.

30:38.680 --> 30:41.411
- Jesus Christ.
- Come on. I...

30:42.240 --> 30:44.846
I ain't askin' much. A sofa, that's all.

30:55.280 --> 30:58.124
All right. So I'm not good enough
for your shitty trailer, is that it?

30:59.240 --> 31:01.686
Lord, you get them hackles out fast.

31:03.040 --> 31:04.690
Well, you're young.

31:05.360 --> 31:07.203
World's gonna have its way with you.

31:07.960 --> 31:10.611
Knock some of that strut out of you,
that's for sure.

31:11.280 --> 31:12.700
I ain't afraid of you.

31:12.800 --> 31:15.201
I ain't the one
you ought to be afraid of.

32:02.840 --> 32:06.208
If you're gonna eat my cereal
and read my books, make some coffee.

32:24.840 --> 32:26.604
That's the local regiment.

32:28.160 --> 32:29.446
Met a sorry fate, too.

32:33.440 --> 32:35.363
Shit, you seen this one?

32:40.360 --> 32:42.966
Twelve years old, David Shelton.

32:43.080 --> 32:44.491
Shelton?

32:44.880 --> 32:46.928
There's four of 'em
in this regiment, see?

32:47.240 --> 32:50.323
Father, three boys.

32:51.880 --> 32:53.564
It's your kin.

32:56.560 --> 32:58.927
So, they all died?

32:59.320 --> 33:01.163
Even the boy?

33:02.480 --> 33:04.801
Why kill him? He was just a kid.

33:08.560 --> 33:10.483
'Cause a nit makes a louse.

33:11.720 --> 33:14.405
At least that's what
one of the soldiers said.

33:15.600 --> 33:19.366
Your daddy never told you
about any of this?

33:20.560 --> 33:21.800
No.

33:36.080 --> 33:37.570
Shit!

33:38.520 --> 33:39.851
Be right back.

33:58.560 --> 34:00.483
Rednecks and drugs.

